---
// src/pages/docs/angular/install.astro
import Layout from "../../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Install & Overview - Angular">
  <div class="mb-4 text-sm font-mono text-neutral-500 uppercase tracking-widest">
    @elekcsv/angular
  </div>

  <h1 class="mb-8 border-b-2 border-black pb-4">7.1 Install & Overview</h1>

  <p class="text-xl text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed mb-10">
    The <code>@elekcsv/angular</code> package provides a highly optimized
    <code>CSVImporterService</code>. It wraps the headless <code>@elekcsv/core</code>
    engine, bringing zero-allocation parsing directly into Angular signal-driven
    components.
  </p>

  <h2>Installation</h2>
  <p>
    The package is designed to be UI-agnostic. You get the importer state machine and
    parsing engine; your component renders templates, buttons, and review screens.
  </p>

  <pre><code>npm install @elekcsv/angular @elekcsv/core
# or
yarn add @elekcsv/angular @elekcsv/core
# or
pnpm add @elekcsv/angular @elekcsv/core</code></pre>

  <h2>Why the Angular Service?</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong class="text-black">Signal-Based State:</strong> Access values like
      <code>step()</code>, <code>isLoading()</code>, and <code>hasErrors()</code>
      directly in Angular templates.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong class="text-black">Non-Blocking Pipeline:</strong> CSV parsing and
      validation run asynchronously to keep Angular views responsive.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong class="text-black">Framework-Aligned API:</strong> Service methods map
      naturally to event handlers in standalone or NgModule components.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <div class="mt-16 flex justify-end">
    <a
      href="/docs/angular/basic"
      class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 bg-black text-white rounded-md text-sm font-medium hover:bg-neutral-800 no-underline! transition-colors"
      style="text-decoration:none;"
    >
      Next: Basic Usage
      <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"
        ><path
          stroke-linecap="round"
          stroke-linejoin="round"
          stroke-width="2"
          d="M14 5l7 7m0 0l-7 7m7-7H3"></path>
      </svg>
    </a>
  </div>
</Layout>
